Feature: Governance as Autocatalytic System

  As a community designing governance
  I want systems that produce conditions making more governance possible
  So that regenerative direction accelerates automatically

  Background:
    Given Egregores compete for DAO influence based on governance efficiency
    And the Egregore Harmonization Engine assigns roles: Catalyst, Stabilizer, Synthesizer, Purifier, Oracle
    And Holonic structure nests Micro-Holons inside Meso-Holons inside Macro-Holons
    And Ostrom's 8 principles provide empirical foundation for commons self-governance

  Scenario: Autocatalytic governance produces more governance
    Given Ostrom's principles produce trust
    When trust reduces coordination cost
    Then lower coordination cost enables more cooperation
    And more cooperation produces more trust
    And the cycle continues without external intervention

  Scenario: Holonic structure enables catalysis at multiple scales
    Given Micro-Holon cooperation generates mesoscale coordination capacity
    When mesoscale coordination generates macroscale governance power
    Then governance power flows back as resources to Micro-Holons
    And each scale catalyzes the scales above and below simultaneously

  Scenario: Egregore competition replaces election cycles
    Given influence flows to what's working
    When losing Egregores fade and winning Egregores replicate
    Then continuous evidence-based competition operates
    And governance efficiency improves without fixed election schedules

  Scenario: Evidence-based competition prevents dominance
    Given no single Egregore can dominate the system
    When governance efficiency and ecosystem integration are evaluated
    Then role assignment through Harmonization Engine prevents monopoly
    And diverse approaches compete on measured performance

  Scenario: Intrinsically regenerative autocatalysis prevents destructive cycles
    Given destructive governance systems operate autocatalytically in the negative direction
    And polarization enables nationalist-religious coalition and civil war triggers
    When the community designs governance with intrinsic regenerative direction
    Then the autocatalytic mechanism accelerates beneficial outcomes
    And the same structural pattern that produces failure in extractive systems produces success in regenerative systems

  Scenario: Governance effectiveness is measured continuously
    Given influence calculation depends on governance efficiency
    And ecosystem integration is tracked over time
    When an Egregore's approach loses effectiveness
    Then influence decreases and the approach fades
    And successful approaches gain influence and replicate
    And the community continuously improves without formal review cycles

  Scenario: Local commons connect to regional and global coordination
    Given Micro-Holons represent local biomes
    When Meso-Holons provide regional node coordination
    And Macro-Holons enable global coordination
    Then local commons decisions align with regional capacity
    And regional capacity aligns with global governance power
    And resources flow bidirectionally across all three scales
